'''Adam Łukasz Królikiewicz''' (December 9, 1894 – May 4, 1966) was a [[Poland|Polish]] [[Equestrianism|horse rider]], major of Polish Army, who competed in the [[1924 Summer Olympics]]. He was born in [[Lviv]]. He died in [[Konstancin-Jeziorna]].
He was a member of [[Polish Legions in World War I|Polish Legions]] and fought in [[World War I]].
In 1924 he and his horse ''Picador'' won the bronze medal in the [[Equestrian at the 1924 Summer Olympics|individual jumping competition]]. As part of the Polish [[Show jumping|jumping]] team they finishing sixth in the [[Equestrian at the 1924 Summer Olympics|team jumping competition]].
In 1966 he died in an accident, when he fell from a horse during the filming of [[Andrzej Wajda]]'s film ''[[The Ashes (film)|Popioły]]''.
