'''Joe Blythe''' (1881–?)<ref name="whustats">{{cite web | url=http://www.westhamstats.info/westham.php?west=2&ham=63&united=Joe_Blythe| title=Welcome to the Wonderful World of West Ham United Statistics - Joe Blythe | publisher=www.westhamstats.info | accessdate=26 November 2013}}</ref> was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Half back (association football)|half-back]] for [[Blyth Spartans A.F.C.|Blyth Spartans]], [[Jarrow F.C.|Jarrow]], [[Everton F.C.|Everton]], [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]], [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]]<ref name="forboth">{{cite web | url=http://www.whufc.com/articles/20120203/millwall-match-preview_2236884_2597456 | title=Millwall match preview | publisher=www.whufc.com | accessdate=26 November 2013 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202225003/http://www.whufc.com/articles/20120203/millwall-match-preview_2236884_2597456 | archivedate=2 December 2013 | df=dmy-all }}</ref> and [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].
==Footballing career== Born in [[Berwick-upon-Tweed]], England, Blythe played for Blyth Spartans, Jarrow and Everton<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.evertonfpf.org/players/joseph-blythe/| title=Joe Blythe | publisher=www.evertonfpf.org | accessdate=28 November 2013}}</ref> before moving to West Ham in 1902 and making his debut against [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] on 6 September 1902.<ref name=whustats/> Blythe missed only one game in his first season and played 23 games in his second and final season with The Hammers.<ref name="jb">{{cite web | url=http://spartacus-educational.com/WHblytheJ.htm | title=Joe Blythe | publisher=spartacus-educational.com | accessdate=28 November 2013}}</ref> He joined Millwall for the following season and won the [[London Challenge Cup]] with them in 1909. He made 341 appearances for Millwall before moving to Watford for the [[1911-12 Watford F.C. season|1911-12 season]].<ref name=jb/>
==Managerial career== Blythe was manager of Blyth Spartans before the [[World War I|First World War]].<ref name=jb/>
