'''Lithuanian Plants Genes Bank''' ({{lang-lt|Augalų genų bankas, AGB}}) is plant gene resource guardian and sustainable use organization governed by [[Ministry of Environment (Lithuania)|Lithuania's Ministry of Environment]]. Its headquarters based in [[Akademija, Kėdainiai]], Central [[Lithuania]].<ref>[https://www.118.lt/imones/augalu-genu-bankas/7601738 118: AUGALŲ GENŲ BANKAS]</ref>
In 1997 the plant storage started to operate. In 2004 the Lithuanian Plants Gene Bank was established and the seed storage become a part of it.<ref>[https://www.delfi.lt/grynas/aplinka/augalu-genu-bankas-vieta-kur-saugomas-tikrasis-lietuvos-lobis.d?id=59953565 augalu genu bankas vieta kur saugomas -tikrasis lietuvos lobis]</ref> By 2017 it had 3318 samples from 201 variety of different kind of plants.<ref>[http://www.agb.lt/saugykla.htm Saugykla]</ref>
