'''Pseudovirions''' are synthetic viruses used to inject genetic material, including [[DNA]] and [[RNA]], with specific and desired traits into bacterial and eukaryotic cells. Pseudoviruses are closely related to [[viruses]] in structure and behavior but lack many characterists exhibited by true viruses, including the capability to replicate{{Ref_label|replication|1|a}}.

